<Author>stace120
<Content>Mixed feelings First off I love Hiltons and I travel a lot so I try to be really fair in reviews. Secondly I think that there are probably a lot of different room types at this hotel so that may explain the difference in reviews.This is a very, very busy airport hotel so expect the general qualities found in such- long lines/ waits and sometimes crowds.I arrived late so I had no problem checking in. The front desk staff was very efficient and courteous. I booked a balcony room which meant i could only get 2 double beds. The balcony wsn't really much. There was a tiny door to go out to a three foot wide balcony with a high cement wall and lots of mildew. This was clearly meant for smokers and not for people who wanted to enjoy a balcony.The room itself was pretty dated and not especially clean. I had ordered a bottle of wine online which was not in the room when I arrived. I recieved a phone call from room service at MIDNIGHT wanting to deliver the wine. They argued when I said it was too late, but ultimately did not bring the wine and did not charge me.The business center was very nice. They had everything I needed. It was very spacious and well equipped. Check out went okay, but I did wait a very long time for somecody fromHertz to show up at the bell desk to rent me a car- which I had reserved.All in all, this was a decent experience, but I would try to get an updated room and would not order room service. 
