<Author>Oswego90
<Content>We LOVED this hotel! I had to write this review because our recent experience at the Hilton Miami Airport was so different from the previous reviewer's. We (mother 50's and daughter 23 yrs) booked the hotel for 2 nts. pre-cruise in mid-August. I was able to get a great rate for an Executive Floor room w/ 2 double beds. Maybe this made all the difference. The room was beautiful. The beds were wonderful. The food in the Executive Club was great - and since we stayed during the Olympics, many people were popping in and out of the Club to watch Michael Phelps. Very pleasant, relaxing experience.The weekend staff, too, was wonderful. Check-in was a breeze at the HHonors dedicated desk. The bellmen and concierge staff were friendly and helpful. I had a fun conversation with the shuttle driver as I rode from the hotel over to the airport on Sat. night to meet my daughter's flight. Returning on the shuttle, however, was more problematic. Two or three shuttle vans passed us by because they had filled beyond capacity at the International terminal and had no room for the domestic passengers waiting. Eventually, the hotel sent a shuttle just for us and for the other family who had been waiting with us for quite some time.Sunday, we decided to go to the pool early to catch some sun before the imminent arrival of Tropical Storm Fay. Again, loved the pool...AND the very large(!) iguana who twice visited the pool deck during our stay and seemed quite at home. As others have mentioned, the lagoon surroundings are beautiful and are filled with wildlife - lizards, birds, etc.Negatives: the fact that WiFi access is not free and that food in the restaurant and pool bar is on the expensive side (the drinks at the pool bar were pricey and small).Overall, I would definitely recommend this hotel if you are able to book a deluxe or Executive Floor room. (One more note: we had no trouble at all with airport noise - our room faced east, and the view at night was spectacular.) 
