<Content>Nice hotel for the price The hotel looks a bit dated and could use some freshening up but, overall, we had a very positive experience staying there. We stayed there the night before our Caribbean cruise vacation and the hotel was located just a short drive far from the Miami Cruise Port. As far as safety, we had absolutely no problem there-- the place looked quite safe. The beds were clean and comfortable. The restaurant food was decent, although pricey. The buffet breakfast cost us almost $70 (for two adults and two kids) but it was delicious and offered a lot of variety. There are a lot of parking spaces at the hotel but self-parking will cost you $10 per day + tax. For us, that was the biggest negative. We paid about $145 for the room for the one-night stay and overall it was a very good choice. If we're in the Miami area in the future, we would definitely consider staying there again. 
