<Author>Atl_traveler007
<Content>Don't Pick this Hotel just for the Airport Shuttle! First I will say what was good, or ok with this hotel--the beds were comfortable.However, we couldn't get a room with a bed larger than a twin! Even though the hotel looked to be almost empty. We were told that all the other rooms were booked. Something I don't believe at all. The lobby was empty, the restaurant was empty, the halls were empty, and the pool--it was empty as well!Could it just be that the front desk people don't like it when you book your room through Hotwire? The lady at the front desk mentioned Hotwire two times. Something that I have not seen before.Our main problem with this hotel though, is that we booked it because it was close to the airport, and had an airport shuttle. It took us 45 minutes to catch a shuttle (close to an hour in total to get to the hotel) from the airport. Then the next morning we tried to get the 6:40am shuttle to the airport. When we got to the front there was no shuttle, and there were no bell people in the front area outside the hotel. I went inside to ask about it, and they said it was full so it left early. The next shuttle came sometime close to 7:00AM and the driver quickly mentioned that he was the 7:20AM shuttle, and would be happy to leave 2 minutes early at 7:18AM. Several of us complained and he finally left for the airport. But again, it took us in total about 40 minutes to get to the airport, which is about 4 miles away!The room was not at all what I expected from a so called 4-star hotel. It was very outdated (I remember the cottage cheese type ceiling from the 70's), had very worn carpet and some things in the bathroom that were falling apart. Two electrical outlets I used had plugs that were very loose and pushed way in (away from the covers) with your plug--almost a safety hazard. In the hallway, in the morning, there was a tray of food left over from the night before. The service and cleaning people were about as scarce as the other people in the hotel. There were a few people eating in the restaurant, and we did get good service there. But, the food was about on the level of a cafeteria--not as good as what you can get at Chili's. So in summary, I don't know who would rate this as a 4-star hotel. In fact, I would guess that you will get better service, food, and accommodations at most of the 3-star hotels in the area. 
