<Author>coolcaesar
<Content>Decent rooms, but too noisy and the place needs a renovation The first room they gave me smelled like a smoker's room even though I made it clear at the front desk that I needed a non-smoker's room. Fortunately, the second room smelled fine. The bed was pleasant and comfortable; the bathroom was immaculate and well-maintained; the furnishings and room overall were clean and in good shape. I went out to the fitness center, which is located in its own pleasant little building next to the pool and is open 24 hours. The fitness center is well equipped with a set of free weights, and multiple late-model treadmills and stairmasters, each with its own small flat-screen TV and headphones so everyone can watch what they want without bothering anyone else. The pool area, fitness center, and lobby all look fine. The major downside of this hotel, as numerous other reviewers have noted, is the proximity to the airport. Even though the place is clearly heavily soundproofed, you can clearly hear a distant roar every ten minutes (and sometimes the building shakes). I am a very deep sleeper so I don't mind, but any light sleepers would be well advised to avoid this place. The second big downside is the expensive parking. Because there is no street parking on Blue Lagoon Drive, and all the other parking lots nearby are secured private lots for various corporate office buildings, you have no choice but to pay $10 per day to park in the Hilton's lot. At least they let registered guests go in and out so it's not like you're trapped. As several people have noted, there are no major restaurants nearby (Burger King headquarters is down the street but there's no Burger King to go with it) so you will have to drive a distance if you want something other than room service or the hotel restaurant. Finally, although well-maintained, the hotel is beginning to look dated and in need of a renovation. This is especially obvious in the elevator lobbies and elevators; the control panels both in the lobbies and the elevators are clearly quite battered and need to be replaced. The elevators are also noisy and cranky.I was pleased overall considering that I got a good deal on Hotwire during a weekend when much of Miami was fully booked and the remaining hotels were charging insanely exorbitant rates. But I would not stay at this hotel if I were booking through a regular service like Expedia or Orbitz. 
