<Author>WeekendGetaways43
<Content>Great Mainstay Hotel for Us Have stayed a this Hilton several times. It's a great getaway for us and a good stopover for travelers. We've stayed in an Executive King/ Non-Smoking. Had a great view of the Lagoon and the Miami Skyline. The room has mini-bar, 27 inch TV, work desk area and an easy chair. This hotel has been around for a while but it remains consistently above average even though the furniture appears to be aging. The bed is Great as with all the Hilton Hotels I have stayed in.The best room we had was an Alcove Room (get an upper floor for a nice view) which is very large and also has large screen LCD TV's with wrap around sofa and easy chair - were recently updated for the previous Super Bowl when the Chicago Bears stayed here.The hotel has 14 floors with the first 11 floors having north and south wings. The top 3 floors are considered Tower Rooms and are part of the Executive and HHonors Levels. I love the Breakfast in the Executive Lounge, with Continental Breakfast fare and attentive service.I must admit though, I do not like the coffee. I think they recently changed brands and it is not very good in my opinion. Pool Bar is very good with Marco the bartender a very helpful and kind man. He was fun to talk to.The pool is great for all the family. There is a workout gym with cardio equipment and machine weights ( alas no free weights)We had the Sunday Brunch in the Coral Cafe at $25.95 per person. It is worth the price if you bring a healthy appetite. I find the regular menu a little limited in choices, but the prices are pretty good for hotel fare, as well as tasty. I did ask for variations of the main course I had requested and was quickly accommodated. Wireless internet is 9.95 per day and if service is slow, call the front desk and they will send up a device to help improve the reception ( we were in a wing room on the 11th floor)The staff here is very nice. Front desk service was quick, courteous and painless. The hotel is located not far from a Publix Super Market, CVS Pharmacy ( 24 hour) and some fast food places. Parking is $11 valet/ $7 self-park. Overall, I rate this as a Very Good Hotel with the right amenities and services to earn it a 4 star Hotel. We will return when we need a getaway, but need to remain local. 
