<Content>Convenient location, solid airport hotel鈥?#x201d; Had less than 12 hours total here, transiting from San Juan to back home. Arrived around 7:30p; hotel shuttle came within 10 minutes of my stepping onto the curb at the airport鈥?as per prior posters, do note that hotel shuttles pick up and drop off on Departures level! This means schlepping bags back upstairs from baggage claim.Check in was friendly. I had reserved a king/non-smoking, and reiterated this request at the desk鈥?the gentleman had no king beds, so I asked if I could at least get an airport view鈥?none available, so he upgraded me to Concierge floor鈥?unexpected, as I鈥檝e just fallen back to Blue level at Hilton.My room, with two double beds, was nicely appointed, and certainly clean. Bed linens were sharp looking and quite comfy, sufficient and high quality pillows. Wifi signal was strong. Bathroom stuff was Crabtree  Evelyn.I visited the Concierge lounge around 8:30p, and the hostess was just starting to break down the hors d鈥檕uerves鈥?but she stopped when I came in. I had a really nice appetizer here of coconut fried shrimp and a glass of reasonable, but not great, white wine. I went back to the lobby to get a postcard to send to Kiddo, and was stunned at the absolute scrum in the lobby. HUNDREDS of people, all in formal wear鈥?turns out they were hosting both a high school prom AND a very large wedding reception. I ducked into the deserted The Cove restaurant, where I had a tasty appetizer. Service was crisp and friendly. I was up at 5:30a, and, although they didn鈥檛 open until 6-something, the hostess at concierge lounge connected me with coffee around 5:50a鈥?nice, because she certainly had the option of sending me away until they opened. I went back around 7a and the breakfast spread looked pretty good. They have a pc/printer in the lounge where boarding passes can be printed.Checked out and was on the 7:30a shuttle bus, and away.Solid hotel鈥?I counted 18 consecutive AAA 4-Diamond awards on the wall in the lobby, so they鈥檙e obviously doing things consistently well. I was pleased with the overnight, and would be happy to return if I needed to transit MIA. Employees uniformly helpful and crisp, and the public spaces looked pretty sharp. Good bed, clean room. Not sure how convenient this would be as a Miami business destination, but as airport hotels go, this was really good. If you were doing a night pre- or post-cruise, would be very good. 
