<Content>Enjoy! We booked this hotel for a Saturday and Sunday stay (Jan 1  2) before leaving for a cruise. Although we were disappointed that we didn't book closer to South Beach this hotel was well priced compared to SoBe. And it didn't stop us from enjoying SoBe both days. Arriving very early and hungry, the hotel held all our bags while we enjoyed the breakfast bar and restaurant. Afterwards, officially starting our vacation we laid in the sun by the pool, watched planes taking off, read magazines, and sipped cocktails ordered from the outdoor bar. After some time passed we checked in. The front desk was very helpful when we discovered we forgot to book an extra fifth room for our large group. Being New Year's Day AND a weekend made all of us nervous. In the end the hotel arranged for the extra room with no one having to share. The staff was very friendly, the rooms were very clean and the bedding very comfortable. We never noticed planes during the night. The food was good both in restaurant and room service. The Sunday Brunch was a pleasant surprise and quite excellent. If you can manage to stay on Sunday, do so for the delicious elegant Sunday brunch with all the mimosas you can get away with. This Hilton Hotel is definitely recommended if flying into Miami. Enjoy! 
