<Author>moodyblue
<Content>Mixed feelings I recently finished a 4 night stay at the Miami Airport Hilton. Some aspects of my stay were quite pleasant, and others were clearly not. I had some concern about staying here due to the proximity to the airport. However previous reviews seemed to indicate that this wouldn't be a problem. Well, I really beg to differ! If you have a room facing the airport, you WILL hear airplane noise, and a lot of it. To the hotels credit, they have double pane windows, but that just didn't make much of a difference. I can say from personal experience that there are multiple take-offs as late as midnight and starting as early as 6 am. And on my last night there, I know that there was at least one plane taking off at 3 am. Maybe a room on the back side won't be as noisy, but I wouldn't bet on that. I had a very nice corner suite with a fantastic panaroma view of Miami to the east. The problem there would be for those who want to sleep late. I had to get up early so it wasn't a problem for me, but I could imagine the sun would be quite intense for those hoping to sleep late. The geography might be rough, but those who are light and noise sensitive, should try for a room facing south (away from the airport) and facing west. Due to my lack of desire to go out and eat, I ate at both hotel restaurants. The food was pretty average, but what bothered me more is that for being in south Florida, the menu had virtually nothing on it to highlight nuevo latino cuisine. They could have done so much to provide some exotic dishes, but the menu was pretty much what I'd expect to see in Kansas City. I had access to the towers lounge and both the breakfast and evening spread were also quite average (though free). Alchoholic drinks did cost money, but that seemed to be done on the honor system. It also bothered me that I received no recognition for being a Hilton Hhonors Diamond member. One night out of the four, I had turn down service. What happened to the other three nights? And, though the room was officially listed as non-smoking, the smell of stale cigarette smoke was unmistakable. Would I stay there again? For one night - yes; multiple nights - no. 
