<Content>Great pre-cruise stop over We booked a Carnival Cruise for Christmas including airfare. Our flight got us into Miami the night before the cruise (Dec. 18). The cruise line put us up at the Miami Hilton along with several hundred other cruisers. I was pleasantly suprised by the hotel. Check-in was a breeze, the hotel lobby was attractive and inviting. The room was spacious (although there wasn't much of a view). We weren't bothered by airplane noise from the nearby airport. I've had some bad experiences at hotel's in Miami so this was a welcome change.We enjoyed walking along the nearby lagoon. There was a nice bar off the lobby that was comfortable. We ate dinner at the nicer restaurant in the hotel. It was pricey, but well prepared and presented. The cruise lines allowed us to check in for the cruise in the lobby the next morning. Although it was a bit disorganized (not the hotel's fault), we left feeling rested and relaxed and ready for a week in the Caribbean. If you have to stay at a hotel near the airport or are booking a pre-cruise stay, I recommend the Hilton Miami Airport. 
