<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Fine hotel for a quick visit Booked a one night pre-cruise stay as our flight into Miami did not arrive until 10:00 p.m. We were basically looking for a nice, clean, safe place to stay for one night that offered 24 hour room service. Complimentary airport shuttle to hotel was terrific. We didn't wait more than 5 minutes before it arrived at the airport for pickup. Delivered us to the hotel front entrance within 10 minutes. Check-in was courteous, and professional. The room was clean and spacious, including the bathroom. Not fancy, but certainly not shabby. Room service ordered at 11 p.m. arrived in 20 minutes and was perfect. Noise was not an issue at all. Once in awhile you could hear the faint sound of a loud plane, but for the most part we forgot the airport was so close by. Booked our room on the Hilton website for the Bounceback rate, which included full buffet breakfast for two. Breakfast buffet was very nice and a great value for the extra $5.00 per person in the room rate. We enjoyed the pretty pool area and spa after breakfast. Pool water temperature could be heated a bit more, but the spa was wonderfully warm and soothing. The hotel also has a small gym and sauna next to the pool area. The concierge booked us a shuttle to the Port of Miami cruise pier for $8.00 per person which worked very well for us. All in all, no complaints. I would recommend this hotel to pre-cruise travelers or for those who need to stay overnight near the Miami International Airport. 
